## Summary

The `KanbanBoard` spec defines a card that represents a Kanban board, a visual project management tool used to track the progress of tasks or projects. This card allows users to create and manage columns, add tasks, and move tasks between columns.

## Import

```js
import { KanbanBoard } from '../kanban-board';
```

## Usage as a Field

The `KanbanBoard` can be used as a field within a consuming card or field. For example:

```js
import { CardDef, field, contains } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { KanbanBoard } from '../kanban-board';

export class MyCard extends CardDef {
  @field kanbanBoard = contains(KanbanBoard);
}
```

## Template Usage

To use the `KanbanBoard` within a template, you can simply include the `KanbanBoard` component:

```hbs
<KanbanBoard @model={{this.kanbanBoard}} />
```

The `@model` argument should be bound to the `kanbanBoard` field from the parent card.
